<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-25T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-25T18:00:00-05:00" n="180" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d180">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">511.3B1/9: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate
                                    Peace</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-25T23:00:00+00:00"><hi rend="italic">October 25,
                                        1919—11 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 11:28
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>4824. Your 3469, October 17th, 5 p.m. Commission shares Department’s
                            views as to nature and [effect of] protocol to Arms Traffic Convention,
                            and informal discussion shows that Principal Allied and Associated
                            Powers understand protocol in same sense. Polk.</p>
                        <closer><hi rend="smallcaps">American Mission</hi></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>